{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2d02a8fa-72b4-4251-9c67-8997967f4b50","content":"There's no existing pipeline in this repo, so here's the general guidance for the migration:\n\n### Migrating from `VSTest@3` to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n**1. Update your `.csproj`** — add the new test runner:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <UseTestingPlatform>true</UseTestingPlatform>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**2. Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`** in your pipeline YAML:\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run Tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: 'test'\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >\n      --configuration $(BuildConfiguration)\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=TestResults.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage;Format=Cobertura\"\n```\n\n**3. Publish results & coverage** (unchanged):\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: 'VSTest'\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/coverage.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key differences from `VSTest@3`\n- **No more `.runsettings` for the runner** — configure via CLI args or `<TestingPlatformOptions>` in the project file.\n- `dotnet test` drives the new platform natively; `VSTest@3` is not compatible with it.\n- TRX logger and code coverage collectors work the same way via `--logger` and `--collect`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"561d091e-863e-46a2-8126-d98da3d71073","outputTokens":437,"requestId":"67E9:247AEF:29D1756:2E1C460:69FD345F"},"id":"d1563a70-2774-4b1c-ada2-df932850772c","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:55:06.122Z","parentId":"235564f7-aca1-4221-89e6-f84bc315ac20"}
